            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Protein</td>
                <td>2g</td>
                <td>4g</td>
            </tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>

    <p>While the protein content is lower than traditional wheat flour, the added fiber and nutrients make it a healthier option for gluten-free baking.</p>

    <h2>FAQs About King Arthur Gluten-Free Bread Flour</h2>

    <div class="faq">
        <h3>1. Is King Arthur Gluten-Free Bread Flour safe for celiacs?</h3>
        <p>Yes, King Arthur Gluten-Free Bread Flour is certified gluten-free by the GFCO and is produced in a dedicated gluten-free facility, making it safe for individuals with celiac disease.</p>

        <h3>2. Does it contain any allergens?</h3>
        <p>The flour is free from gluten, but it does contain rice, which is a common allergen for some individuals. Always check the label if you have other food allergies.</p>

        <h3>3. Can I use this flour for all types of baking?</h3>
        <p>Yes, this flour is versatile and can be used for bread, pizza dough, muffins, and more. However, it may require slight adjustments in recipes to achieve the desired texture.</p>

        <h3>4. How does it compare to other gluten-free flours?</h3>
        <p>King Arthur Gluten-Free Bread Flour is specifically formulated for bread-making, offering better structure and elasticity compared to single-ingredient gluten-free flours like almond or coconut flour.</p>
    </div>

    <h2>Conclusion</h2>

    <p>King Arthur Gluten-Free Bread Flour is a safe and reliable option for individuals with celiac disease or gluten sensitivity. Its GFCO certification, dedicated gluten-free facility, and high-quality ingredients make it a trustworthy choice for gluten-free baking. While it may have a slightly different nutritional profile compared to traditional wheat flour, its versatility and performance in recipes make it a valuable addition to any gluten-free pantry. Whether you’re baking bread, pizza, or muffins, King Arthur Gluten-Free Bread Flour can help you create delicious and safe gluten-free treats.</p>

